Feb 19 2008 	Pleased with the Olympic House Hotel	I booked this hotel based on the reviews on this site, so I thought it was fair to make my own review of the hotel.The hotel is very near Paddington rail and underground station and it's a short walk from there to Sussex Gardens. The hotel is located next to other hotels, some shabby, some more known as the Days Inn.We were greeted by a friendly woman behind the reception and check in was quick thanks to the fact that we've booked everything via hotelopia.com. We were given room 605, which was downstairs from the main entrance, near the breakfast room.The room was a double room, with two beds. It wasn't a big room, but it was clean and the furniture looked new. The beds were maybe a little to hard for someone's comfort, however I slept in worse beds. The badroom was small, but clean, with a great shower and new clean towels everyday.I think the room can be warm during the summer, but now the temperature was okay. Being downstairs near the breakfast room means that people are walking past your room from quite early in the morning, so if you are a light sleeper, make sure you get another room or get earplugs. While in the room, we heared a rumbling and after a while we realised it was the tube underneath. It wasn't disturbing by the way, just a funny thing to notice.Breakfast was very poverish, only cheese, ham, serials, jams, butter and toast. Don't drink the orange juice, it looks okay but doesn't taste like orange juice. Although breakfast wasn't all that, I didn't expected it to be, so no disappointment from me here. (You can always eat breakfast at Garfunkel's near Paddington Station...)All in all, you get what you pay for, but I found it worth the money while citytripping London. Clean rooms, conveniently located and great rates. I will definitely use this hotel the next time.	
