Nov 25 2007 	Perfect stay at the Olympic House Hotel	I booked the Olympic House Hotel in August 2007 for a three night stay in November. The booking process was simple and complication free, apart from one problem, at time of booking I emailed the hotel and stated that I would require parking, I have stayed along this strip previously (Sussex Gardens) and know that the parking that each hotel has is limited. I contacted the hotel about a week before to confirm that parking would be fine as requested and I was informed that there was no parking available which really threw our trip into turmoil as there was very few spaces left in any other hotel. I mention this issue only to stress the importance of ensuring that the parking is reserved for you and emails are not 'lost'. Although the biggest point to make is that as soon as the issue arose it was dealt with by the fantastic manager Andrea who completely took the issue on and assured me that it would be solved, which it was, she gave us her space, which we kept until there was parking available. We actually managed to stay in this space the entire stay by parking in such a way as to accommodate two cars. Parking issue aside, the hotel interior was immaculate throughout, very clean and new, everything and more you can expect from this price range. As previously mentioned we had stayed at other hotels in this strip that weren't as nice as this. The room was small but they always are here and its all we needed, it was very well presented and had a new flat screen wall mounted tv. It is worth noting that the mattress was quite hard so may be uncomfortable for some. There was also one pillow each and no extras offered which was an issue for me as I always need more. The bathroom again was immaculate and the shower was modern and of good quality. The breakfast was the usual, continental breakfast, cereal, toast, egg, cheese and ham. Of good standard and was more than enough. If you're not a fan of being made to sit on other peoples tables beware though as one of the breakfast staff did tend to cram people together. All in all I would definitely stay here again, good value at around £200 for three nights, immaculately presented throughout and a very helpful manager, and not to mention a fantastic location, just a 2 minute walk to Paddington tube station. (just ensure that if you have a car, make absolutely sure parking is available).	
