Aug 31 2007 	Great clean hotel	This hotel was refurbished a few months before we stayed so everything such as the sink, toilet, shower (with detachable shower head), bed, carpets, TV, wallpaper, etc, seemed brand new, clean, and modern. I'm really picky about how clean a hotel is, so I was very pleased by how new everything was. Even the elevator was new, so riding on it was very quick and smooth.We stayed a week on the 3rd floor and we were facing the street and there were other hotels on the other side of the road. The street was fairly busy at most hours of the day and night and even with the window all the way closed, you could still really hear the cars and other vehicles going by. It didn't really bother us that much and we still slept well despite the noise from the passing cars. Infact, since it was summer, we slept some nights with the window opened a little since we didn't want to waste eletricity using the A/C. The air conditioning/heater unit itself looked modern and brand new and there was a nice control panel for it on the wall next to the door.The only negative thing I could say about our room was the size. We had a double room and the room itself and bathroom were quite small compared to what I was used to in America and some other places I've stayed in Europe. But it didn't detract from our overall experience though. I just wanted to mention it for anyone reading this review who might be more picky about the size of their room, especially the bathroom.There was still enough room to walk around and unpack our things. There were plenty of drawers in the room to store items and a decent sized closet for clothes and other items. And besides, I'd very much rather have a small but very clean room like we had instead of a large but dirty room like some of the other places I've stayed in the US and Europe. The bed was more than big enough for both of us and it was comfortable and the sheets, pillows, and blankets were very clean.The LCD TVs had satellite service, so there were a nice variety of channels available to watch and some of those channels played some recent big blockbuster movies for free, so that was nice.The breakfast room is clean and organized just like what is shown in the photos. The breakfast staff was friendly and the food was good and fresh. There were two types of cereal available (Corn Flakes and Rice Crispies, I think), toast, eggs, milk, and orange juice. There may have been more but that's what I can remember. The staff would bring the toast to you warm and fresh instead of having it sit there for a long time. Good service.I really liked the location of this hotel because it was only a few minutes walk from Paddington Station, which has a direct train to and from Heathrow, so getting to the hotel from the airport was amazingly quick and easy. Also, there were plenty of good sit-down restaurants and pubs extremely close to the hotel and a Burger King and Subway restaurant if you prefer cheap fast-food. In addition, there were markets and a big name grocery store very close if you wanted to buy food and take it to eat at Hyde park or back to your hotel room.All in all, we really enjoyed our experience at this hotel and I would gladly stay here again next time I visit London due to its location and how clean it was.	
